item.title: Help with codes and commands
item.dc:creator: @Encouragin Encouragin
item.description:
@Encouragin wrote:

If your requesting a command and want to learn on how to create a command, Here’s an example of a command in wL sources:

/**
 * A basic command written in Java.
 */
if (command.equals("hello")) {
           System.out.println("Hello World.");
}

With this command, it will prints out ‘Hello World’ in your batch file. If you wanna learn more, have a visit at the Java tutorials which are located on Java.com site.
